4: Tch! Pretty quick for such a big dog!
14: If you don't want to get eaten, that is.
18:
Rufo never lets a target escape. Just
give up.
22: Go ahead, Rufo. Eat it all.
31:
I thought you needed help... Hope I
didn't get in your way.
40: And thank you to your wolf, as well.
48: It's a pleasure to meet you. I'm Stella.
58:
I'm Alk, nice to meet you. Are you out
hunting monsters, too?
62:
I'm on my way to Palpebra.
...I didn't take your job from you, did I?
65:
Go ahead and take credit for it. With
that last one down, I've already
taken care of all the monsters here.
70:
...We were told there were quite a
few roaming around, but you're
saying you handled all of them
yourself?
75:
There were a lot, yes... But, I heard a
cry for help, so I had to.
78:
A cry from the... animals of the
forest. I don't expect you to believe
me, though.
88:
...I took care of the monsters before
anything could happen to them.
95:
...You're a weird group, huh? Like, just
in general.
100:
Less weird than some brat
wandering the forest with a magical
gun. What's your story?
104:
...I'm on a journey searching for the
owner of this gun.
107:
Here's the wanted poster. There's a
tattoo on the back of their right
hand... Have you ever seen this
before?
112:
...Sorry, I don't believe we have. If
you're looking for the owner of a
cryptic artifact, though, the Guild
might be able to help you.
116:
Well, that's assuming it was actually
registered and not smuggled out...
122:
Wait, do you know something about
this gun?!
126:
I uh... I don't know for sure, but it
certainly SEEMS like a cryptic artifact.
129:
That's good enough! Any lead is
good enough!
139:
...I have only one reason for what I'm
doing.
142:
I'm going to take this gun, and with
Rufo's help... We're going to kill the
owner.
146:
That bastard used this gun to kill
Rufo two years ago.
149:
...I don't remember all the details.
When I came to, the attacker was
gone, and all that was left was this
gun and...
159:
...I don't know. All I know is that Rufo's
still suffering. I want to set Rufo free.
163:
That's why I'm going to find and end
that killer. No matter what.
174:
Does she know what you're trying to
do?
177:
You're still a child and don't fully
understand what you're doing. You
should return home, and—
181: "We can get you a new dog."
184:
She said that so many times. I know
she's just trying to comfort me, but...
187:
But Rufo's my best friend. My only
friend! You can't just replace a friend
like that!
190:
I've been looking for clues for so
long... Please, let me come with you.
195:
...Light. The kid's determined. He's not
going to give up just because you
told him to.
205: We won't help you kill anybody.
208:
But you have a right to feel how you
do, so we won't stop you either. Is
that okay?
224:
Th-this place... Is this real? Did I fall
and hit my head or something?
228:
You can take any room you'd like
that doesn't already have someone
staying in it. Just don't tell anybody
about this place, okay?
232:
...I won't. But can I write to my
grandmother just to let her know
that I'm doing okay?
235:
I know this is all my fault to begin
with, but I don't want her to worry.
240:
Aww. What a sweet little grandma's
boy!
